<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="696" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6724:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at
                                    Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-18T12:00:00+01:00">November 18, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November
                                    18—9:19 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>63. To my 61, November 15, 4 p.m., should be added that Weygand still
                                insists against doing anything that might embarrass the Pétain
                                Government.</p>
                            <p>De Gaulle is to return shortly from Africa to London. One of the
                                matters to be discussed with him there is the delicate problem of
                                defining his future position in case General Weygand joined the
                                British.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>